(14, 4, 9, 'God is calling you', 'god-is-calling-you', 'Untabbed', 'GOD IS CALLING YOU', 'pic-postulantes  22.jpg', '<p>GOD IS CALLING YOU</p>\r\n<p>According to the &nbsp;&nbsp;Larousse dictionary, vocation is an inclination, a particular inclination for a certain kind of life, a type of activity. It is an act by which God calls every person for a determined role, which constitutes his end, &nbsp;this includes the call to the priesthood or religious life.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Vocation is an inspiration, an interior motion by which God calls a well-determined person to a state or a form of life. So it is God who takes the initiative even though there may be human mediations. The one who is called must listen and be able to answer. So there is an interaction between the two. When God calls someone, he gives the person a mission to fulfill for Him, and sometimes even imposes conditions on the person. For instance, the call of Abraham and Moses in the bible,(Commission episcopale des vocations Rwanda 2003).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Abraham\'s vocation: Gn12,1-5</strong>. God calls Abraham to leave everything to go to the country that the Lord will indicate to him. By faith, Abraham obeyed this call. The one called cannot know everything before hand so he has to trust God and respond with faith.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The vocation of Moses: Ex 3:1-12</strong>. God calls Moses to go to the people of Israel to free them from oppression of the Egyptians; Moses made excuses because he felt inadequate for the job God asked him to do. It is true&nbsp; that by himself he was inadequate. God often calls us to a task&nbsp; that seems too difficult&nbsp; but he doesn&rsquo;t ask us to do it alone. He offers us his support and other resources needed just as he did with Moses &nbsp;We see that it is God who calls a person and the person responds. His response engages the person for life because vocation is an event that decisively and forever transforms the existence of the &nbsp;person.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; The vocation of Jeremiah: Jer 1:4-10.</strong> God chose Jeremiah when he was still in his mother&rsquo;s womb so Jeremiah\'s mission was to find out what God wanted to do with him each day. Maybe you too, God has already called you, but you &nbsp;do not understand and do not know where and what he is calling you to do. That is why for young people, each time you read the scriptures you must ask yourselves, what does God want us to do for him today?</p>\r\n<p>God said to Jeremiah,\"before forming you in your mother\'s womb I knew you, before you came out of the womb I consecrated you as a prophet of nations ...\" Today, God addresses this same message to young people: long before your birth, he thought of you and has a plan with for you like for Jeremiah. Do not be discouraged even if life seems hard; remember that God thinks of you every day, he has a plan for you, and you are valued in his eyes. Like for Jeremiah, God promises that he will be with you and he will empower you to carry out His mission. We are all called for a particular mission. For Jeremiah, It was to be prophet of the nations. And you, what mission is Jesus Christ giving you today?</p>\r\n<p>You too need to see your entire life as a mission. May you recognize what this message of God is for you.The message from Jesus that God wants you to deliver to people through your life! Allow yourself to be transformed and let yourself be renewed by the Spirit so that this may be possible, and so that your beautiful mission is not compromised. &lsquo;&rsquo;The Lord will accomplish it in spite of your weaknesses, provided that you do not abandon the path of love and that you are always open to his supernatural action, which purifies and illuminates \". Pope Francis, Gaudete et exsultate, n&deg; 23-25.</p>\r\n<p>`1 AMANI&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>'),
