(23, 3, 3, 'The first sisters', 'the-first-sisters', 'Untabbed', 'The first sisters', 'pic-face6.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">The beginnings ...</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">For the Cardinal, the apostolic participation of the sisters has always been very important.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">\"Despite all the enthusiasm of the missionaries (priests), their efforts will never bear the fruit that is expected, unless they are helped by women who minister to women.\"</font></font></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">In 1867, the terrible famine and the accompanying epidemics decimated the people of Algeria.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Hundreds and then thousands of orphans were brought to Catholic priests and the archbishop himself, who accepted them all and entrusted them to the care of priests and sisters.</font></font></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">144th anniversary of the Congregation of the Missionary Sisters of the Blessed Virgin Mary, Queen of Africa</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">On September 8, 1869, that is 144 years ago, on the feast of the Nativity of the Blessed Virgin Mary, a group of 8 young girls from Brittany came to Algiers.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Their arrival was a response to the appeal of the Archbishop of Algiers, Cardinal Charles Lavigerie, who wanted to fund a new missionary congregation working in Africa and for Africa.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">He understood perfectly well the importance of the apostolate among women and saw its leading role in changing African society.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">during the voyage from France to Algeria, the young sisters experienced terrible moments, because there was a great storm at sea.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">It was a preview of what awaited them in Africa.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">When they found out on the day of their arrival that they were the first and only sisters to work for the new congregation, one of them exclaimed, \"Well, if it\'s only us, it\'ll be fun!\"&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Extremely hard work was waiting for them,&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">poverty and discomfort.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">The first Superior General, Sr. Marie Salome, also came from Brittany.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">She came to Algiers in January 1872. She became Superior General in 1882. She was a good educator for the orphans entrusted to her care, demanding, but kind and loved.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Then he led the community as mother general with great wisdom and dedication.</font></font></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">As on the first journey, the Sisters of the Missionaries of Our Lady, Queen of Africa, are often in the midst of a storm today, but like the pioneers, they continue their mission without giving in to adversity, as Mother Marie Salome said:</font></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">\"Love for Christ impels us to great things and to desire what is more perfect.\"</font></p>'),
